06/05/2003
SARANDE, Albania -- Authorities have introduced tighter sanitary controls at checkpoints along the Greek border in the Sarande district, in a bid to prevent the spread of SARS (Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome). 
On Monday (5 May), several inspectors were deployed to the checkpoints. 
Sanitary inspectors will also provide controls at the port of Sarande. 
(Albanian Daily News - 06/05/03; ATA - 05/05/03)
